stylometry: Standard deviation is important because it allows you to see how close the data points are to the average. It is especially important in a simulation model when using RISKSIMTABLE because it allows you to compare this to the average. Just because one of the simulations has a higher average doesn't mean it is the best possible solution if the standard deviation is also high. If the standard deviation is also high, this means that the data is widely spread out. It is important to weigh the differences between the average and standard deviation. An answer with a lower average and a low standard deviation may be a better solution than a high average with a higher standard deviation.
